ENTRY       EC 2.6.1.79                 Enzyme
NAME        glutamate---prephenate aminotransferase;
            prephenate transaminase (ambiguous);
            PAT (ambiguous);
            L-glutamate:prephenate aminotransferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring nitrogenous groups;
            Transaminases
SYSNAME     L-arogenate:2-oxoglutarate aminotransferase
REACTION    L-arogenate + 2-oxoglutarate = prephenate + L-glutamate [RN:R07276]
ALL_REAC    R07276
SUBSTRATE   L-arogenate [CPD:C00826];
            2-oxoglutarate [CPD:C00026]
PRODUCT     prephenate [CPD:C00254];
            L-glutamate [CPD:C00025]
COMMENT     A pyridoxal-phosphate protein. Aspartate can also act as the amino donor, but more slowly (cf. EC 2.6.1.78, aspartate---prephenate aminotransferase). The enzyme from higher plants shows a marked preference for prephenate as substrate compared to pyruvate, phenylpyruvate or 4-hydroxyphenylpyruvate [1].
